name: NAD+ synthase (glutamine-hydrolysing)
classes: Carbon-nitrogen ligases with glutamine as amido-N-donor
reaction: ATP + deamido-NAD+ + L-glutamine + H2O = AMP + diphosphate + NAD+ + L-glutamate [RN:R00257]
comment: NH3 can act instead of glutamine (cf. EC 6.3.1.5 NAD+ synthase).

references.title: Pathway of diphosphopyridine nucleotide biosynthesis in Escherichia coli.
Biosynthesis of diphosphopyridine nucleotide. III. Nicotinic acid mononucleotide pyrophos-phorylase.
